This paper deals with the issue of achieving an efficient dynamic mapping in vehicular networking scenarios, which involves the use of networked sensors and algorithms to estimate the positions and trajectories of connected vehicles in a certain area. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.LG), and computer vision (cs.CV). Given the focus on networked systems and control algorithms, cs.NI and cs.SY are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of machine learning and computer vision techniques to improve positioning accuracy suggests that cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CV are also relevant.
